- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the impact of carrier aggregation on spectral efficiency. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possibility as the paper mentions the use of small cells in heterogeneous networks. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possibility as the paper discusses the peak data rate in cellular networks. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still a possibility as the paper may touch upon security concerns in HetNets.
